headline: 1 Insurance Stock on Our Watchlist and 2 to Think Twice About
summary: Insurance companies serve as the backbone of risk management, providing essential protection and financial security for individuals and businesses. But worries about an economic slowdown and potential claims deterioration have kept sentiment in check, and over the past six months, the industry’s 3.7% return has trailed the S&P 500 by 1.7 percentage points.
